# DEPRECATED — kin no longer emits ssh Host blocks here.
#
# Hostnames are not unique across fleets; this file's unqualified
# `Host <machine>` stanzas shadow silently when the operator
# manages more than one kin repo (arch-ssh-config-namespaced).
#
# Replace:   Include <repo>/gen/ssh/_shared/config
# with ONE:  Include ~/.config/kin/*/ssh-config
# then run:  kin login <user>
#
# That writes ~/.config/kin/bir7vyhu/ssh-config with fid-qualified
# `Host <machine>.bir7vyhu` blocks (collision-free across fleets).
# `kin ssh`/`kin deploy` never read either file — they discover
# the operator cert via ssh_identity().
#
# This stub will be removed in a future release.
